Practical drawing classes will take place in the natural environment, at different outdoor sites, in museums and in the classroom. Students learn how to depict nature, architecture, various details and plants according to the task.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of speciality-oriented drawing practice is to develop drawing and sketching skills pursuant to the needs of the speciality as well as to study the various ways of depicting urban and natural landscapes.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course the student: - can create a consistent composition in their work; - can see the whole picture as well as the details; - knows how to use different tools and how to find the tools necessary for depicting the motive of their choice
